rginalities they deal withRe-evalutates Romanticism in the light of marginalityPinpoints the interface between Classicism, Romanticism and Modernity  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 24. Mai 2022) 4aLiterary Studies. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh1 aBone, Drummond, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aCamilleri, Anna, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aFranklin, Caroline, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGross, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHaekel, Ralf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalmi, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aJames, Robert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLansdown, Richard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLennartz, Norbert, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aLessenich, Rolf, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMinta, Stephen, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aMole, Tom, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aO’Neill, Michael, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aShears, Jonathon, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aTuominen-Pope, Josefina, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aWolfrum, Friederike, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertEdinburgh University Press Complete eBook-Package 2018z978311078043740uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/9781474439435?locatt=mode:legacy40uhttps://www.degruyter.